column1: BC Mushrooms_InFORM_Fall 2017 - Samples are Dried and Homogenized
Champignons de C.B., InForm 2017, automne 2017 - les échantillons sont séchés et homogénéisés
Notes: Samples are freeze dried thoroughly, then ground to a powder using a mortar and pestle. Radionuclide concentrations are calculated with the wet weight
Notes: Les échantillons sont lyophilisés à fond, puis broyés en poudre à l'aide d'un mortier et d'un pilon. Les concentrations de radionucléides sont calculées avec le poids humide
A variety of mushroom samples were collected by citizen scientists from Northern Ontario
Samples were received air-dried. For ease of homogenisation, they were further dried under high-vacumm for several days, then ground in a mortar and pestle.
